d but I\'d be singing bubbles on my own longingly looking to the away fans wishing I was among them they made a racket whatever the score, great fans. I remember going to goodison on a monday night it was freezing,  ludek miklosko got sent off and julian dicks went in goal his first action was picking the ball out of the net after facing a penalty,  we lost 31 and I think sky gave dicksy man of the match. When I got older I moved back down south and getting my son and myself our 1st season tickets it was like winning the lottery,  one of the best away days my wife had booked tickets to see Russell Howard in Birmingham,  the first thing I done was to see who westham had that day, we had wba at the hawthorns,  they were 3 nil up at halftime, scotty parker apparently went mad at them halftime we came back and drew 3 3 it was like winning the fa cup!  Another quick story I was visiting family in Anfield we went to the arkles pub I was wearing a westham shirt and a load of Bordeaux fans walked in they were playing liverpool in the champions league that evening apparently they quite liked westham so after a few beers I ran back to my mums I had a load of westham shirts there I gave them out the Bordeaux lads were made up at about 7pm they gave me a ticket to go the game with them, they all had there westham shirts on and I had taught them bubbles which I had them singing at Anfield in the away end , the liverpool fans and some players looked really confused,  I thought it was hilarious liverpool smashed them I think 4 or 5 nil but a really funny experience,  there are loads of things I could tell you about getting out of work last minute to go to a game or being sneaky checking the results,  bit I\'ve spoke enough thanks for reading gavin. Come on you irons'),(2829,55,203,'tandc','1'),(2830,55,203,'privacy-cookie','1'),(2831,55,203,'g-recaptcha-response','03AGdBq24EedatZjNVkt3aCdkvVPweTE8qj9NJCtQh7_BywsN6hN2FjqiS5xa-6oiS7vSR_EUpKUncFCswhU0oV0RVGC_bnjEZV629fvWEkaacd73lXF7O