ew that his brain was functioning. While he was in hospital his bed was festooned with Wolves scarves and memorabilia. All of his Get well cards were Wolves related and many from his friends had drawn with images of the Wolves. One of his school friends contacted the Wolves to see if any of the team could visit. It was unfortunate that they arrived for a visit the days he was discharged from hospital after 14 weeks. After intensive phsiotherapy and speech therapy and with much determination he relearned all his skills e.g walking, talking etc. He also had 2 further operations to higher his eyelid which was completely closed and to straighten his left eye. After some time he was allowed to be a mascot a  Wolves game and was so proud to walk out with Geoff Palmer. As a family we were treated to seats at the game and wonderful Wolves hospitality. It was a day to remember. Since his recovery Mark has never missed a home game and attended 90% of away games. He is a season ticker holder and has every programme neatly stacked. His passion for Wolves has passed down the generations in the family and now aged 47 will be a Wolves fan forever.    Gillian Simmons'),(6315,55,452,'tandc','1'),(6316,55,452,'privacy-cookie','1'),(6317,55,452,'g-recaptcha-response','03AGdBq25RTk57hpjszuFV9O-12wpcZnYt_2C4jXzeaH7O9dkvtTD6HNqxrDof4KKz6ndXyaoZDw0tL-J7P3b4kwnElBHTtFFy9LVXFt5YESeyrgDsHDmydXxOXfjngMegBMZzZ82w87QPq-9CP5RS4ocV4vrXwqmlxCclInH4oIevavtIOnwhnKap8S2mgii_xHnoXeSdOmyUUQXc5aYL_dkeqOS2n7cOjyQRnWA7pVwCtqEWXURu3Vj07bn2Rp6Gvrmg3i-V_V6XMrIcz7uoUlvvZdPEkwFq219ZW6993UdtUQigCVkVWP8Z3TIEvkynhTsJ_TJH1W0kNHOrQfQjBIvm8drjsezCZhj86gUbnYXkqXKcvSzpvOouAoRZEuH1dLIsksM1giwNnGhg7mCnt2RJ4qLMAwimeLgOXYfpeQFORnwlUuYEhyfc-4rbo_g4c-MjWrxo44II4Gu2rD-3PZD3KykjNb-pDA'),(6318,55,452,'submit_time','2020-10-31 15:07:38'),(6319,55,452,'submit_ip','2.220.129.128'),(6320,55,453,'first-name','Zubair'),(6321,55,453,'last-name','Khalid'),(6322,55,453,'contact-number','07447447225'),(6323,55,453,'email-add','virgo_vic