e, unfortunately Jose and Porto were too good on the day.\r\nAnd here is where my story begins. \r\n\r\nA year later we get Barcelona in the last 16, star studded Barca who were just starting their run on europe, the Games where in March, but I had a football tournament in Lloret de Mar a few weeks later so was absolutely gutted when I found out we were staying in Barcelona and were just going to miss it, luckily Celtic got through and into the quarter final, they had seen the mighty Barcelona off over the 2 legs with barca players at that time, Ronaldinho, Xavi, Cocu, Puyol, overmars, luis Enrique, Victor valdes, Reizinger, Saviola and Andreas Iniesta on the bench, then my luck changed we have drawn a lesser known spanish side in the quarter finals, a frustrating 1-1 first leg at parkhead, i am off to lloret de Mar at 14 years old for my teams football tournament, we have a budget given to us for spending each day we are there, 3 games we have are against Barcelona Juveniles, Juventus Juveniles and a German county team, but that isnt what is on my mind, first 2 days as all the other lads are spending their budget each day on things the shouldnt and this group of lads were all different from 2% beers to arcade machines to laser pens to ornamental swords, as I keep mine to try and put a plan of action together, day 3 and no game, Go Karting and the Camp Nou was the plan put together by the coaches, I pretend Im not feeling great so I am going for a sleep, as I look out from my balcony to make sure the team bus is away and soon as its out of sight Im straight out the room down to reception and onto a bus to the train station, I board the train and the journey has started, how naive I was I thought maybe an hour, 4 and a half hours later I arrive in Villarreal with not one idea where to go and what to do, luckily I bump into a group of Celtic fans who take me under their wing and of to the game we go, we get in and game starts, down 1-0 after 6 minutes and never got st