:\"1\";}','2020-10-30 10:30:06'),(343,55,'a:12:{s:12:\"cfdb7_status\";s:4:\"read\";s:10:\"first-name\";s:5:\"Rowan\";s:9:\"last-name\";s:5:\"Burke\";s:14:\"contact-number\";s:11:\"07885685041\";s:9:\"email-add\";s:29:\"athotm_ail_dotcom@hotmail.com\";s:10:\"birth-date\";s:10:\"1987-09-17\";s:9:\"address-1\";s:18:\"8 Wheatfields Road\";s:9:\"town-city\";s:7:\"READING\";s:8:\"postcode\";s:7:\"RG2 9DG\";s:10:\"your-story\";s:2862:\"As a man born and bred in South East England, I of course support (glory glory) Manchester United. I mean, what sense would it make to support a team nearby, such as Reading with the Madejski literally 3 minutes from my house? None, right? \r\n\r\nNow, you could argue that staying a fan of the Red Devils for the past 7 years makes me the nation&#039;s biggest football fan because, let&#039;s face it, it&#039;s all been pretty atrocious since Sir Alex skipped his merry way out of OT. Or reluctantly hobbled. Definitely reluctantly hobbled. But I&#039;ve been an avid supporter since I was about 4 so would never give on the boys, despite their best efforts to deter some fans. \r\n\r\nAnyway. \r\n\r\nNow, I&#039;m far from an anomaly being a United supporter from outside the parameters of Salford, but one such story about my journey to watch my beloved team should show my dedication and sheer passion of live football. \r\n\r\nFebruary 2018 my wife was heavily pregnant, but I managed to get my hands on tickets for the FA Cup draw against Reading. Firstly, as I mentioned the Madejski is literally just up the road from me, but I ended up driving 5 hours north to watch Reading play, which makes about as much sense as Gary Lineker endorsing crisps. And secondly, it was during a week of intense snow storms. \r\n\r\nMy wife said she was happy for me to go to the game, but on the basis I came back the same day; mainly due to our antenatal class being booked in for 10am the day after that I absolutely HAD to be back for. I navigated the snow-plagued roads up north for the 8pm KO, enjoyed United displaying a slightly wet albeit convincing 2-0 win, then went to venture home at about 10:30pm. Yet upon locating my car in the car park I was elated to find that I was the lucky winner of a break in, and my window had been smashed in with a few belongings removed from where they belonged. What a treat! \r\n\r\nSo, with all garages closed and car insurance hotlines finished for the day, I ushered all the shards of glass under the seat and found a convenience store to purchase some cling film, which I wrapped in abundance around my rather draughty passenger door. At about 11:30pm I was finally in a position to venture home through the intense snow with only a few layers of plastic wrap separating me from the bitter elements. At this point I would like to take the opportunity to mention that cling film provides precisely zero noise cancelling functionality. \r\n\r\nA very loud, very cold, very low vision, very late night, much longer than anticipated journey later I was finally in bed next to my snoozing wife, absolutely shattered, borderline frozen, but happy I had made it and would be present and eager for our baby class the following day. \r\n\r\nOh, but I had an email in the morning saying the class was cancelled due to the snow. \r\n\r\nI must really love football. \";s:5:\"tandc\";s:1:\"1\";s:14:\"privacy-cookie\";s:1:\"1\";}','2020-10-30 10:30:57'),(344,55,'a:12:{s:12:\"cfdb7_status\";s:6:\"unread\";s:10:\"first-name\";s:16:\"Lorenzo Nicolas \";s:9:\"last-name\";s:6:\"Danila\";s:14:\"contact-number\";s:11:\"07511693599\";s:9:\"email-add\";s:25:\"danilalorenzo41@gmail.com\";s:10:\"birth-date\";s:10:\"1994-06-15\";s:9:\"address-1\";s:15:\"Lower hester 44\";s:9:\"town-city\";s:11:\"Northampton\";s:8:\"postcode\";s:6:\"Nn26bl\";s:10:\"your-story\";s:5:\".....\";s:5:\"tandc\";s:1:\"1\";s:14:\"privacy-cookie\";s:1:\"1\";}','2020-10-30 10:32:28'),(345,55,'a:12:{s:12:\"cfdb7_status\";s:6:\"unread\";s:10:\"first-name\";s:7:\"Car