h year to Swansea on his birthday and we have been lucky to get to games. Chris has followed Swansea all over the country and he loves an away day. He has seen Swansea rise up the league and he was over the moon when Swansea were promoted to the prem and could meet West Ham. Another of his proudest memories would be when we all went to Wembley to watch Swansea play Bradford in the cup final where they won 5-1. Chris always says its funny going to Swansea games because the other fans all have there thick welsh accents and give him a funny look when hes singing Hymns and Arias at the top of his voice. All in all Christopher is mad about Swansea and all because my dad was best man at a wedding there. His room is covered in Swansea memorabilia and he is proud of being different to most Londoners. \";s:5:\"tandc\";s:1:\"1\";s:14:\"privacy-cookie\";s:1:\"1\";}','2020-10-31 13:29:12'),(456,55,'a:12:{s:12:\"cfdb7_status\";s:6:\"unread\";s:10:\"first-name\";s:11:\"Christopher\";s:9:\"last-name\";s:6:\"Coelho\";s:14:\"contact-number\";s:11:\"07850207422\";s:9:\"email-add\";s:29:\"christophercoelho22@gmail.com\";s:10:\"birth-date\";s:10:\"1993-06-04\";s:9:\"address-1\";s:20:\"12 hamlyn house High\";s:9:\"town-city\";s:7:\"Feltham\";s:8:\"postcode\";s:11:\"   TW14 4GA\";s:10:\"your-story\";s:354:\"My name is Christopher and I&#039;m the biggest football fan because I go to every home and away matches. I am a Manchester United fan from London as you know travelling to Manchester to watch home games is very difficult but I always go to support my team even though I have 3 kids but I always go and watch Manchester to play because I care about them \";s:5:\"tandc\";s:1:\"1\";s:14:\"privacy-cookie\";s:1:\"1\";}','2020-10-31 13:50:32'),(457,55,'a:12:{s:12:\"cfdb7_status\";s:6:\"unread\";s:10:\"first-name\";s:4:\"Dean\";s:9:\"last-name\";s:8:\"Marsland\";s:14:\"contact-number\";s:11:\"07932623985\";s:9:\"email-add\";s:24:\"deanmufc@btopenworld.com\";s:10:\"birth-date\";s:10:\"1960-03-22\";s:9:\"address-1\";s:30:\"Flat 2, Moss Manor, The Avenue\";s:9:\"town-city\";s:4:\"Sale\";s:8:\"postcode\";s:6:\"M334SH\";s:10:\"your-story\";s:1583:\"Ive been going to Old Trafford since 1969 missing approximately 16 home games in all competition&#039;s prior to Covid. Football has come first before everything(see below), cost me many ladies over the years but i  would  never change it \r\n\r\n Been to 17 F.A .Cup finals and Wembley&#047;Cardiff 44 times nearly all watching Manchester United. Also have travelled extensively  to  away games and visited 14 country&#039;s for Champions&#047;Europa League games. Went to Bangkok for a friendly for 3 days. \r\n\r\nThe best trip was 1999, The Treble. We had 2 cars start in Sale, Manchester on the Saturday to drive to the F.A.Cup Final, beat Newcastle then drove to dover and stopping in various places in France and Spain on the way to Barcelona for the Champions League Final. Had 3 days in Barcelona and met up with all the lads. Travelled back on the Thursday ending up at The Belfry , Birmingham on the Saturday night where a mate of mine was the manager. Reluctantly(Liverpool fan) he gave us 3 bottles of Champagne for us to drink in the night club surrounded by lovely ladies. Drove home on the Sunday.\r\n\r\nI have a big programme collection, 100s of ticket stubs and photos of the treble and my best possession&#039;s are Duncan Edwards, Ray Wood and Sir Matt Busbys autographs and a personal signed photo of George Best who i did have the opportunity to meet, also photographed.\r\n\r\nMy only downfall is i did miss a home game to go Christmas Shopping(i was in love) in 1983, Watford at home. Never lived it down\r\n\r\nStill love it and cant wait to get back in football grounds again \";s:5:\"tandc\";s:1:\"1\";s:14:\"privacy-cookie\";s:1:\"1\";}','2020-10-31 14:36:08'),(458,55,'a:12:{s:12:\"cfdb7_status\";s:6:\"unread\";s:10:\"first-name\";s:4:\"Mark\";s:9:\"last-name\";s:7:\"Simmons\";s:14:\"contact-number\";s:11:\"01384292045\";s:9:\"email-add\";s:21:\"SIMMONS_JOHN3@sky.com\";s:10:\"birth-date\";s:10:\"1973-03-17\";s:9:\"address-1\";s:45:\"23 Maidendale Road Kingswinford West Midlands\";s:9:\"town-city\";s:12:\"Kingswinford\";s:8:\"postcode\";s:6:\"DY69DD\";s:10:\"your-story\";s:1884:\"I would like to nominate my son Mark Simmons as Football Fan of the year.\r\nWhen Mark was 7 years old he was involved in a major road traffic accident which resulted in him sustaining multiple life threatening injuries. He had a Blood clot removed from his brain, broken femur and the optic nerve to his left eye severed. After his life saving operation at Corbett Hospital, Stourbridge he was in a coma for over 4 weeks he was  paralysed down the left side. We were told to talk to him during this time and one day I gave him a pen and paper and asked him who was going to win the next game. (  he is a Wolves supporter)It was against Liverpool who were then top of the division. He wrote Wolves win 2-1. We then knew that his brain was functioning. While he was in hospital his bed was festooned with Wolves scarves and memorabilia. All of his Get well cards were Wolves related and many from his friends had drawn with images of the Wolves. One of his school friends contacted the Wolves to see if any of the team could visit. It was unfortunate that they arrived for a visit the days he was discharged from hospital after 14 weeks. After intensive phsiotherapy and speech therapy and with much determination he relearned all his skills e.g walking, talking etc. He also had 2 further operations to higher his eyelid which was completely closed and to straighten his left eye. After some time he was allowed to be a mascot a  Wolves game and was so proud to walk out with Geoff Palmer. As a family we were treated to seats at the game and wonderful Wolves hospitality. It was a day to remember. Since his recovery Mark has never missed a home game and attended 90% of away games. He is a season ticker holder and has every programme neatly stacked. His passion for Wolves has passed down the generations in the family and now aged 47 will be a Wolves fan forever.    Gillian Simmons\";s:5:\"tandc\";s:1:\"1\";s:14:\"privacy-cookie\";s:1:\"1\";}','2020-10-31 15:07:39'),(459,55,'a:12:{s:12:\"cfdb7_status\";s:6:\"unread\";s:10:\"first-name\";s:6:\"Zubair\";s:9:\"last-name\";s:6:\"Khalid\";s:14:\"contact-number\";s:11:\"07447447225\";s:9:\"email-add\";s:26:\"virgo_victorious@yahoo.com\";s:10:\"birth-date\";s:10:\"1987-09-09\";s:9:\"address-1\";s:15:\"131 Eyrescroft \";s:9:\"town-city\";s:13:\"Peterborough \";s:8:\"postcode\";s:6:\"Pe38eu\";s:10:\"your-story\";s:22:\"Biggest Liverpool fan \";s:5:\"tandc\";s:1:\"1\";s:14:\"privacy-cookie\";s:1:\"1\";}','2020-10-31 15:11:59'),(460,55,'a:12:{s:12:\"cfdb7_status\";s:6:\"unread\";s:10:\"first-name\";s:4:\"Paul\";s:9:\"last-name\";s:7:\"Moralee\";s:14:\"contact-number\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"email-add\";s:21:\"nikegolf823@gmail.com\";s:10:\"birth-date\";s:10:\"1988-04-27\";s:9:\"address-1\";s:16:\"3 Kimberly court\";s:9:\"town-city\";s:7:\"Stanley\";s:8:\"postcode\";s:7:\"Dh96fb \";s:10:\"your-story\";s:468:\"On the 16th may 1998 I was due to get married but when Newcastle United reached the final of the fa cup I had to rethink my steps and what happened was I got married left the wedding to attend the match and traveled back to reach my night time party all this was agreed with my beautiful wife however she had no choice I was attending the match regardless! Yes we are still happily married and she knows my football and beloved Newcastle is always going to come first \";s:5:\"tandc\";s:1:\"1\";s:14:\"privacy-cookie\";s:1:\"1\";}','2020-10-31 15:35:05'),(461,55,'a:12:{s:12:\"cfdb7_status\";s:6:\"unread\";s:10:\"first-name\";s:5:\"Jair \";s:9:\"last-name\";s:5:\"Rocha\";s:14:\"contact-number\";s:11:\"07365691017\";s:9:\"email-add\";s:22:\"jairrocha902@gmail.com\";s:10:\"birth-date\";s:10:\"1991-05-19\";s:9:\"address-1\";s:13:\"3allemby road\";s:9:\"town-city