h Wolves with his mate. When he got there he couldnt get a ticket, so being the lad he was, he told the staff at Wolves that he was a scout for Millwall and they let him in.\r\n\r\nApart from his Fianc and kids, Dannys life was football. It was all he ever talked about and would travel the country every week to watch a game.\r\n\r\nTragically, Danny passed away just a few months ago and left behind two heartbroken kids that he adored, Jack & Jacey.\r\n\r\nIf I won, Id donate the prize to his kids.\";s:5:\"tandc\";s:1:\"1\";s:14:\"privacy-cookie\";s:1:\"1\";}','2020-11-07 02:53:52'),(616,55,'a:12:{s:12:\"cfdb7_status\";s:6:\"unread\";s:10:\"first-name\";s:7:\"Michael\";s:9:\"last-name\";s:6:\"Doonan\";s:14:\"contact-number\";s:11:\"07368666420\";s:9:\"email-add\";s:18:\"doonan@hotmail.com\";s:10:\"birth-date\";s:10:\"1989-11-13\";s:9:\"address-1\";s:20:\"41 langside gardens \";s:9:\"town-city\";s:7:\"Polbeth\";s:8:\"postcode\";s:12:\"West Calder \";s:10:\"your-story\";s:4445:\"As a young football fan 17 years ago at the age of 13 I experienced something, that I thought at the time would happen many times in my lifetime and would experience it again, unfortunately not (yet) as a young lad we would get to as many games as possible be it Celtic, Celtic reserves or U19s game almost 3&#047;4 nights a week as well as playing or training other nights, the reserves and u19s played their games in livingston and if they didnt have games I would go watch Livingston play, I was football daft, everything was always football and I was lucky enough to have a dad and grandfather who would take me to those games, other plans were cancelled and they seen to my every need. This particular year celtic went on a crazy European run and managed to progress into the Uefa Cup final, that was it I had to go, only one thing stopping me was an immaculate school attendance record which I was very proud of never missing a single day, we had got flights and it allowed me to get into school and back out after being present, away we go to Seville, my grandmother would have went berserk if she knew I wasnt at school, all the names where being taken of who was there by the national newspaper so we had to make up 2 names, what an experience it seemed all so simple to do, but now the cost must have been extravagant, we push in without a ticket and got the game, unfortunately Jose and Porto were too good on the day.\r\nAnd here is where my story begins. \r\n\r\nA year later we get Barcelona in the last 16, star studded Barca who were just starting their run on europe, the Games where in March, but I had a football tournament in Lloret de Mar a few weeks later so was absolutely gutted when I found out we were staying in Barcelona and were just going to miss it, luckily Celtic got through and into the quarter final, they had seen the mighty Barcelona off over the 2 legs with barca players at that time, Ronaldinho, Xavi, Cocu, Puyol, overmars, luis Enrique, Victor valdes, Reizinger, Saviola and Andreas Iniesta on the bench, then my luck changed we have drawn a lesser known spanish side in the quarter finals, a frustrating 1-1 first leg at parkhead, i am off to lloret de Mar at 14 years old for my teams football tournament, we have a budget given to us for spending each day we are there, 3 games we have are against Barcelona Juveniles, Juventus Juveniles and a German county team, but that isnt what is on my mind, first 2 days as all the other lads are spending their budget each day on things the shouldnt and this group of lads were all different from 2% beers to arcade machines to laser pens to ornamental swords, as I keep mine to try and put a plan of action together, day 3 and no game, Go Karting and the Camp Nou was the plan put together by the coaches, I pretend Im not feeling great so I am going for a sleep, as I look out from my balcony to make sure the team bus is away and soon as its out of sight Im straight out the room down to reception and onto a bus to the train station, I board the train and the journey has started, how naive I was I thought maybe an hour, 4 and a half hours later I arrive in Villarreal with not one idea where to go and what to do, luckily I bump into a group of Celtic fans who take me under their wing and of to the game we go, we get in and game starts, down 1-0 after 6 minutes and never got started after that, we couldnt really with all the great players we had we couldnt get the ball and it was all being orchestrated by a little magician, technically unbelievable and I was mesmerised, the funny thing of it all he was deemed surplus to requirements because of the EU quota at the team we put out the round before Barcelona, Juan Roman Riquelme what a player, technically never seen nothing like him. While he orchestrated the game another 2 ex Barcelona players done their job at either end Pepe Reina in goal and Sonny Anderson netted to make it 2-0. The unknown team from spain gave us a pasting, little did I know their was a man hunt for me in Barcelona, reported missing, once I arrived back at the hotel there was faces of relief but all I wanted to do was go to bed gutted, we had lost. Any 14 year old thinking about going sneaking of to a game, at least tell someone, would I do it again as a 14 year old boy tomorrow knowing the final score was a loss and worry that I caused? Absolutely,  seeing Riquelme was worth it all. \";s:5:\"tandc\";s:1:\"1\";s:14:\"privacy-cookie\";s:1:\"1\";}','2020-11-07 04:30:03'),(617,55,'a:12:{s:12:\"cfdb7_status\";s:6:\"unread\";s:10:\"first-name\";s:7:\"Stephen\";s:9:\"last-name\";s:7:\"Roberts\";s:14:\"contact-number\";s:11:\"07565214826\";s:9:\"email-add\";s:18:\"robbox5@icloud.com\";s:10:\"birth-date\";s:10:\"1976-06-12\";s:9:\"address-1\";s:19:\"22 Coventry Avenue \";s:9:\"town-city\";s:10:\"Liverpool \";s:8:\"postcode\";s:7:\"L301qu \";s:10:\"your-story\";s:37:\"Im Liverpools biggest fan ever \";s:5:\"tandc\";s:1:\"1\";s:14:\"privacy-cookie\";s:1:\"1\";}','2020-11-07