he last year, Ann wrote to Man Utd over and over wanting to get something special for her Dad. He watched every match but he never got to go and see them play in person. It was too expensive with four kids.\r\nThe two of them would sit together and he laughed at her vocal enthusiasm. They had pet nicknames for footballers. Ann very much misses watching football with her Dad, nobody else gets their humour. This has been a hard year, keeping track of games but missing her partner in crime. He used to know all the teams and their games, International and National. But as others slipped away, he still could recall the matches of his favourite team. He loved many sports, played squash, canoed and was a good footballer himself. Scoring a hat trick in one memorable match. Supported Ann as an indoor climber by driving her to competitions. But football and Man Utd was his first love. With Love from all of us Kevin, always Football Fan of the Year even in heaven. He will still be watching.\";s:5:\"tandc\";s:1:\"1\";s:14:\"privacy-cookie\";s:1:\"1\";}','2020-11-07 22:09:41'),(657,55,'a:12:{s:12:\"cfdb7_status\";s:6:\"unread\";s:10:\"first-name\";s:4:\"Owen\";s:9:\"last-name\";s:6:\"Druett\";s:14:\"contact-number\";s:11:\"07784442556\";s:9:\"email-add\";s:17:\"odruett@gmail.com\";s:10:\"birth-date\";s:10:\"1998-08-29\";s:9:\"address-1\";s:14:\"9 pottery lane\";s:9:\"town-city\";s:17:\"Heworth&#047;York\";s:8:\"postcode\";s:8:\"YO31 8SR\";s:10:\"your-story\";s:275:\"I once watched my team- Manchester United. Whilst I was out watching a game for my local non league side. And whilst screaming YAAAAAYYYYY!!!! For Manchester United scoring, the team playing my local team scored (Whhooopsey), and everyone looked but I didn&#039;t care. GGMU.\";s:5:\"tandc\";s:1:\"1\";s:14:\"privacy-cookie\";s:1:\"1\";}','2020-11-07 23:06:13'),(658,55,'a:12:{s:12:\"cfdb7_status\";s:6:\"unread\";s:10:\"first-name\";s:4:\"Adam\";s:9:\"last-name\";s:7:\"Durrant\";s:14:\"contact-number\";s:11:\"0798242130