14:\"52 Braids Walk\";s:9:\"town-city\";s:4:\"Hull\";s:8:\"postcode\";s:8:\"HU10 7PD\";s:10:\"your-story\";s:2473:\"Charlotte is my daughter and she is only 13 but I think she is the biggest football fan ever. She has loved football since she was about 5 and I have no idea where the love of footie came from as me and her dad had never been into it ourselves. She started in a club after school as the only girl there at age 6 and I saw her a couple of times after leaving work early and could see how much she enjoyed it and didnt care that she was the only girl. She always wanted footie kits for birthday and Christmas and started collecting match attack cards and building her knowledge of players and clubs. At age 8 I decided that I needed to find if there were and girls clubs and another girl in her class had started playing for one so she went there to try out and has played junior girls football in the East Riding league ever since. In the under 10 team her team got to the final and won plus she won most improved player, the following year she won coaches player of the year. She plays fifa and any other football app that she has found too. She eats sleeps and breathes football. She has always supported younger players at the clubs she has been at and supported and helped new team members which was noticed by her coach. She always takes part in fund raising events and charity events for the club. She would love to play professionally in the future and is currently doing very well in the U14 s up until the lockdown has stopped grassroots again. During the first lockdown she did struggle with not being able to see friends and play football but has a sponge one so practiced skills inside and also had me outside in the garden practicing getting past a defender, me, or scoring with me in goal, thats scary! She hasnt had an easy time at school as there arent many girls who Play football and even less who love football with a passion and likes to discuss the latest news and