te about. \r\nHe&#039;s been the captain of his football team several times and has been playing football his whole life. His first word was actually football...well &quot;bootball&quot; because he couldn&#039;t really speak at that age. And when he was about 2, he stole a football from woolworths while his mums back was turned away for a second and wondered off, only to be found playing football with the local fire brigade down the road, who&#039;d called in about a lost little boy that had just wondered up to them and asked if they wanted to play.\r\nWe&#039;re expecting our first baby in June 2021 and he&#039;s so excited to take this little baby to Chelsea games and Plymouth Argyle games  and start a story with him and his child just like he had with his dad. This will be their thing and I love that. \r\nOn the weekend he &#039;asked me out&#039; we went to Plymouth. Our plan was to spend a night in a hotel and go out to a really nice restaurant that night, just for a change of scenery from our small country town. But the next morning his friends rang him up and said they were coming into Plymouth for a home game and did he want to take me to the Argyle game. I said why not, it might be interesting as I&#039;d never been to a football game before. So, one day into &#039;officially&#039; being his girlfriend and I&#039;m standing in the rain at Plymouth Argyle not really understanding the rules but having an absolutely hilarious time. Danny made sure I was ok the whole time too. I did enjoy it, the atmosphere was amazing but I think I might be a fair weather attendee if I go to a match again. \r\nThis would mean the world to him if he won. He&#039;s such a wonderful person, and he&#039;ll be such a wonderful dad. This is the least I can do for him to show him how much he means to us all. \";s:5:\"tandc\";s:1:\"1\";s:14:\"privacy-cookie\";s:1:\"1\";}','2020-11-11 12:57:32'),(793,55,'a:12:{s:12:\"cfdb7_status\";s:6:\"unread\";s:10:\"first-name\";s:8:\"Beverley\";s: